      • save

        public void save()
        Create a new managed rack in Abiquo. This method wil discover the blades configured in the UCS. If the data provided for the connection is invalid a UcsRack will be created in Abiquo but with no Physical Machines attached to it.
        See Also:
        http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/RackResource#RackResource-CreateanewUCSRack< /a>

      • update

        public void update()
        Update rack information in the server with the data from this rack. The IP data member cannot be updated. If changed will be ignored and the old IP will remain.
        See Also:
        http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/RackResource#RackResource#RackResource- UpdateanexistingUCSrack

      • listOrganizations

        public List<Organization> listOrganizations()
        Retrieve the list of organization in this UCS rack. The credentials in the UcsRack configuration might not have enough rights in the UCS to retrieve all organizations. Then only the allowed ones are returned. This data is not persisted in Abiquo.
        See Also:
        http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/

        public void associateLogicServer(String bladeName,
                        LogicServer logicServer,
                        Organization organization)
        Associate a Service Profile and a Blade in UCS. If the Service Profile is already associated then the request cannot be completed. This data is not persisted in Abiquo.
        See Also:
        http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/RackResource#RackResource- AssociatelogicserverwithabladeinUCS

      • cloneAndAssociateLogicServer

        public void cloneAndAssociateLogicServer(String bladeName,
                                LogicServer logicServer,
                                Organization organization,
                                String logicServerName)
        Clone and associate a Service Profile and a Blade in UCS. If the Blade is already associated then Abiquo will dissociate it first. If the request cannot be completed successfully the Blade might be left with no Service Profile associated. This data is not persisted in Abiquo.
        See Also:
        http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/RackResource#RackResource- CloneandassociateLogicServerwithabladeinUCS

      • associateLogicServerTemplate

        public void associateLogicServerTemplate(String bladeName,
                                LogicServer logicServer,
                                Organization organization,
                                String logicServerName)
        Instantiate and associate a Service Profile Template and a Blade in UCS. If the Service Profile is already associated the request cannot be successful. If the Blade is already associated then Abiquo will dissociate it first. If the request cannot be completed successfully the Blade might be left with no Service Profile associated. This data is not persisted in Abiquo.
        See Also:
        http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/RackResource#RackResource- AssociateabladewithaLogicServerTemplate
